# ⚙️ Requirements

If running locally (without Docker):

* Python 3.10+
* pip
* OpenCV
* PyTorch
* Ultralytics YOLO
* FastAPI (backend)
* Node.js (frontend)

---

# 🐳 Run with Docker (Recommended)

## 1. Build all services

```bash
docker compose build
```

---

## 2. Start system

```bash
docker compose up
```

---

## 3. Run in background

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

---

## 4. Stop system

```bash
docker compose down
```

---

# 📷 Run Edge AI only

```bash
docker run -it vwatch-main-edge_ai
```

With restart protection:

```bash
docker run -d --restart unless-stopped vwatch-main-edge_ai
```

---

# 🎥 Camera Configuration

Inside `config/edge_config.json`:

```json
{
  "source": 0,
  "fps": 15,
  "speed_limit_kmh": 60,
  "display": true
}
```

### Source options:

* `0` → webcam
* RTSP URL → CCTV camera
* video file path → offline testing

---

# 🧠 YOLO Model Info

* Model used: `yolov8n.pt`
* Location: `/app/yolov8n.pt`
* Loaded using Singleton pattern (only once in memory)

---

# 📊 System Flow

```
Camera → Stream Handler → YOLO Detection → DeepSORT Tracking
      → Violation Engine → Evidence Generator → Backend API
```

---

# 🚨 Types of Violations Detected

* 🚗 Overspeeding
* 🚦 Red light violation
* 🛣️ Wrong direction driving
* 🚧 Lane violation
* 🔍 Vehicle plate detection (ANPR)

---

# 📸 Evidence Generated

For every violation:

* Frame snapshot
* Cropped vehicle image
* License plate image
* Optional video clip
* Metadata (time, location, speed, type)

---

# 🌐 Backend Integration

Make sure backend is running at:

```
http://localhost:8000
```

Or set in environment:

```bash
BACKEND_URL=http://your-server-ip:8000
```

---

# 🔐 Environment Variables

| Variable        | Description        |
| --------------- | ------------------ |
| CAMERA_ID       | Camera identifier  |
| LOCATION        | Camera location    |
| BACKEND_URL     | Backend API URL    |
| YOLO_MODEL_PATH | Path to YOLO model |
| DISPLAY         | Show video window  |

---

# 🧪 Troubleshooting

### ❌ YOLO not loading

* Ensure `yolov8n.pt` exists in `/app`

### ❌ No video output

* Set `"display": true`
* Check camera source

### ❌ Docker slow build

* First build is heavy (OpenCV + PyTorch)
* Subsequent builds will use cache

---

# 🛡️ Stability Tips (IMPORTANT)

* Use restart policy:

  ```bash
  --restart unless-stopped
  ```

* Avoid multiple YOLO instances

* Do not modify Dockerfile frequently

* Keep model inside container

